content.comment:
Hi,

Can you explain how this line works?

\begin{aligned}
\min_{h:\mathbb{E}_{\mathbb{P}_E}[h]=0} \left\{\mathbb{E}_{\mathbb{P}_E}[hD] + \lambda_2\cdot \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x},\mathbf{x}'\sim\mathbb{P}}\left[\frac{\nabla_x h(\mathbf{x})^\top}{1+h(\mathbf{x})} k(\mathbf{x},\mathbf{x}') \frac{\nabla_x h(\mathbf{x}')}{1+h(\mathbf{x}')}\right] \right\}\\
= & \min_{h:\mathbb{E}_{\mathbb{P}_E}[h]=0} \left\{\mathbb{E}_{\mathbb{P}_E}[hD] + \lambda_2\cdot \mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{x},\mathbf{x}'\sim\mathbb{P}_E}\left[\nabla_x h(\mathbf{x})^\top k(\mathbf{x},\mathbf{x}') \nabla_x h(\mathbf{x}')\right] \right\}.
\end{aligned}

